<p>I am using the below code to grab data from a wordpress RSS feed. However I am having an issue with grabing the 'media file' from the feed.</p>  <pre><code>&lt;?php         $rss = new DOMDocument();         $rss-&gt;load('http://www.ipa.co.uk/rss/jobs');         $feed = array();         foreach ($rss-&gt;getElementsByTagName('item') as $node) {             $item = array (                  'title' =&gt; $node-&gt;getElementsByTagName('title')-&gt;item(0)-&gt;nodeValue,                 'desc' =&gt; $node-&gt;getElementsByTagName('description')-&gt;item(0)-&gt;nodeValue,                 'link' =&gt; $node-&gt;getElementsByTagName('link')-&gt;item(0)-&gt;nodeValue,                 'date' =&gt; $node-&gt;getElementsByTagName('pubDate')-&gt;item(0)-&gt;nodeValue,                 'image' =&gt; $node-&gt;getElementsByTagName('enclosure')-&gt;item(0)-&gt;getAttribute('url'),                 );             array_push($feed, $item);         }         $limit = 20;         for($x=0;$x&lt;$limit;$x++) {             $title = str_replace(' &amp; ', ' &amp;amp; ', $feed[$x]['title']);             $link = $feed[$x]['link'];             $description = $feed[$x]['desc'];             $date = date('l F d, Y', strtotime($feed[$x]['date']));?&gt;             &lt;div class="col-md-4 job-item"&gt;                 &lt;div class="job-item__inner"&gt;                     &lt;?php                     echo '&lt;h2 class="job-title"&gt;&lt;a href="'.$link.'" title="'.$title.'"&gt;'.$title.'&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;';                     echo '&lt;small&gt;&lt;em&gt;Posted on '.$date.'&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/p&gt;';                     echo '&lt;p&gt;'.$description.'&lt;/p&gt;';                     echo '&lt;img src="'.$image.'"/&gt;';?&gt;                 &lt;/div&gt;             &lt;/div&gt;         &lt;?php } ?&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I have seen <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/13923137/display-media-files-from-a-wordpress-rss-feed">this answer</a> on SO which helped me add in the <code>getElementsByTagName('enclosure')-&gt;item(0)-&gt;getAttribute('url')</code>. However its not displaying any img src. I think 'enclosure' is correct as I get errors if I change it to something like this <code>getElementsByTagName('media')-&gt;item(0)-&gt;getAttribute('url')</code></p>  <p>The issue must be that I'm targeting the wrong area of the feed. But I'm not sure what to add to get the image displaying.</p>